The following companies had unusual
price changes in  Peru  trading. Stock symbols are in parentheses,
and share prices are as of the close of trade.  The  Lima General Index (IGBVL)  dropped 0.2 percent to 20,905.80.
The MSCI All Peru Capped Index dropped 1.1 percent to 2,706.62.  Refineria la Pampilla SA  (RELAPAC1 PE), a unit of Repsol
YPF SA known as Relapasa, fell 1.5 percent to 66 centimos after
crude slumped to an eight-month low in  New York .  Candente Copper Corp. (DNT)  , a Canadian exploration
company, rallied 1.9 percent to 54 cents. The shares gained
after copper advanced in New York, according to Hernando Pastor,
an analyst at Lima-based Kallpa Securities SAB.  Panoro Minerals Ltd. (PML)  , a Canadian copper and gold
exploration company, climbed 1.5 percent to 69 cents.  Southern Copper Corp. (SCCO)  , Peruâ€™s biggest copper
producer, advanced 1.3 percent to $29.79.  To contact the reporter on this story:
